*Just a little Wizard Strategy there folks* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/udwarkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dwarkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(6/24/01 11:08:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair donation for a corpse drag or lock pick?</span><hr size=1> Rogues are always in groups I am involved in.  As the threads allude to, each class has something to bring to the group.<br>
<br>
As for charging for a classes capabilities, mine never do it.  I don't ask for &quot;donations&quot; for binds, and characters that can do it often hang out in bind zones for a few minutes just to see if anyone needs a bind.  I never ask for &quot;donations&quot; for resurrections, but being a struggling cleric I will accept them.  I have even cancelled the trade following a resurrect for some folks (unthinkable to those that charge for a bind!), you never when a little kindness to a low-to-mid character will come back to you from a higher level one.  <br>
<br>
Reputation in this game is basically the most important thing your character(s) own.  It gets you in groups where others don't, it gets you into the guild you have chosen, and often determines how folks treat you in game.<br>
<br>
Just a bit of opinion from your neighborhood dwarf.  It and 2 pp leaves you with 2 pp.<br>
<br>
Dwarkon Forgeguard<br>
