Solace Keep <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ukokuten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kokuten</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.livejournal.com/userpic/74980 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(6/27/01 1:33:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.livejournal.com/userpic/74977 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair donation for a corpse drag or lock pick?</span><hr size=1> As a cleric recently YORKED through the levels to 46 (I spent a solid week in a drunken haze of drolvargs, paladins, and monks..  I racked up nine levels in 7 days), I find myself capable of providing a valueable service to the denizens of norrath- the 50% rez.<br>
<br>
My case in point occured last night, as we were gearing up for a two-group mini-raid on SkyShrine. During the prep period, I had a fairly good idea of what my job was going to be (buff and heal the tanks, what?), so when I got a call from a member of a guild I have a lot of respect for, in the zone literally across the hall from me (Cob Scar), I got permisison from my raid leader, a fresh clarity and wis buff from our chanter, and hoofed it. <br>
<br>
I rezzed her ENTIRE group, save for her. she asked me, via tell, how much cash I wanted. My response, which I'm retyping from memory, was <br>
<br>
&quot;No more than fifty plat per person, but less is TOTALLY fine&quot;<br>
<br>
I don't have a problem hoofing it across all of Norrath to help people out. But, my time is valuable. One rouge said it's his Job to pull corpses from tricky spots, well, it's my job to rez people, and to heal and buff, and by Brell, I expect to get PAID for it. When I'm in a group, this payment is normally half loot and exp, half non-tangible stuff like fun, friendship, and &quot;experience&quot; (not character exp, player experience). <br>
<br>
but by god, when I truck my happy dwarven arse, sans benefit of sow, across the frontier mountains to rez you on the ledge in OT from my bind point at the druid ring in DL..  I'm endangering my OWN life.. and folding quite a bit of my OWN time into the endeavour..  I do excpect recomensation, and count it as only fair.. <br>
<br>
but, when I don't get it, I smile, wave, and leave. <br>
and drop another entry into the /ignore. <br>
<br>
keep in mind, my opinions in no way reflect that of my guild<br>
